Practical:3.3 Aim To create an interactive Android application that uses fragments to divide the screen into multiple sections, allowing users to input data in one fragment and display it in another fragment dynamically.
Problem Statement Develop an Android application containing two fragments inside one activity:
              •	Input Fragment: Accepts user input (e.g., name, message)
              •	Display Fragment: Shows the entered input in real-time when a button is clicked.
This demonstrates fragment interaction, dynamic UI updates, and fragment lifecycle understanding.

Open Android Studio → New Project
Select Empty Views Activity
Project Configuration:
Name: FragmentCommunicationApp
Package: com.example.fragmentsapp
Language: Java
Minimum SDK: API 21
Finish and wait for Gradle sync.

